Use pnpm, not npm

# Architecture Rules

## Stack
- Next.js App Router + TypeScript
- No backend, no DB, no auth in V1
- Persistence: `localStorage` only

## Data Model

```ts
interface Trade {
  id: string;
  date: string;       // ISO string
  symbol: string;
  entry: number;
  exit: number;
  pnl: number;
  setup: string;
  grade: string;
  notes?: string;
}
```

## File Structure

```
app/
  page.tsx              # Trade list + filters
  add/page.tsx          # Add trade form
components/
  TradeTable.tsx        # Renders list of trades
  TradeForm.tsx         # Add/edit form
  TradeFilters.tsx      # Filter by setup/grade
lib/
  trades.ts             # localStorage helpers (load/save)
  pnl.ts                # PnL calculations
  format.ts             # Display formatting
types/
  trade.ts              # Trade interface
```

## Rules

- Components are small and focused: layout, form, table, filter
- UI components only render data — no business logic inside
- Business logic lives in `lib/`
- No repository pattern, no service layer, no global state unless needed
- No premature abstraction
- Prefer flat file structure over deep nesting

## Core Loop (build in this order)
1. Add trade form
2. Save to local state
3. Persist to localStorage
4. Render trades in table
5. Filter by setup and grade

## Non-Goals (V1)
- Broker integration, real-time data, cloud sync, AI, advanced analytics
